To use this script, create a file called charGradient.txt in the same directory as the .py file. 
This file should include 1 line of characters, and should be in order of the pixel brightness level that each character is supposed to represent.

For example:
  charGradient.txt contents (rightmost character being a space):
  @%8*;:^=~-_ 
  
  Results from gradient.jpg (included in testImages):
